In this article, First Lady Dr. Jill Biden addresses the National Cancer Institute (NCI) and expresses gratitude for their work in cancer research and treatment. She acknowledges the impact of cancer on individuals and communities, sharing her personal experiences with the disease. Dr. Biden praises NCI for their dedication to the Cancer Moonshot initiative, advancements in studying the immune system, and support for clinical trials. Despite the challenges posed by the COVID-19 pandemic, NCI has continued its efforts in uncovering the effects of the pandemic on cancer rates and finding ways to carry on their work. Dr. Biden concludes her speech by quoting poet Gwendolyn Brooks, emphasizing the importance of unity in the fight against cancer and assuring NCI of the President and her support in their mission to end the disease.